<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese PLA Logistics Department Director Visits Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese Vice Premier Phan Van
Khai, and Defense Minister Doan Khue, today met respectively with
the visiting Director of the General Logistics Department of the
Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA), Wang Ke.
</P>
<P>
Expressing their welcome to Wang, who is also a member of
Central Military Commission of the People's Republic of China,
both leaders noted that Wang's visit is a clear reflection of the
friendly relations between the two armies.
</P>
<P>
Wang, who arrived here Thursday at the invitation of the
Vietnamese army, said that China attaches great importance to
developing good relations between the two armies as well as that
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Good neighborly relations and mutual development are not only
in the interests of both countries, but will also contribute to
world peace and stability and development, he said.
</P>
<P>
Wang has also met his Vietnamese counterpart, Ngu Yen Phuc
Thanh, and is scheduled to visit a number of Vietnamese provinces
before leaving. 
</P>
</TEXT>
