<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Collection of Deng's Funeral Documents Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- A collection of major documents
related to the funeral of China's late leader Deng Xiaoping has
been published and will be distributed nationwide March 4.
</P>
<P>
The People's Publishing House has published the collection in
order to express the profound grief and mourning of all the
Chinese people over Deng's death, on February 19 in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The documents include "A Letter to the Whole Party, the Whole
Army and Chinese People of All Ethnic Groups", issued by the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress, the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Congress, and the Central Military
Commission, President Jiang Zemin's eulogy to Deng Xiaoping at
Deng's memorial meeting, the full text of a life story of Deng, a
name list of Deng's funeral committee, three announcements issued
by Deng's funeral committee, a letter from Deng's family to
President Jiang and the CPC Central Committee, as well as two
editorials carried respectively by "People's Daily" and the
"People's Liberation Army Daily" on February 26. 
</P>
</TEXT>
