<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls For Faster Development in Central, Western China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin today calls
for accelerating development in central and western China during
his meeting today with legislators from Gansu province and Ningxia
Hui Autonomous Region, both in northwestern China.
</P>
<P>
On the first day of the Fifth Session of the Eighth National
People's Congress, China's top legislature, Jiang came to join NPC
deputies from remote Gansu and Ningxia in their panel discussions
on the government work report, and on how to bridge the gap
between eastern and western China to achieve common prosperity.
</P>
<P>
The deputies spoke highly of Premier Li Peng's government work
report, which they termed as a realistic and inspiring report
permeated with Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics and the guidelines of the Fifth and Sixth
Plenum of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, these deputies aired views and suggested ways and
means on narrowing the gap between the eastern and western
regions, retooling of state-owned enterprises and ethnical unity.
</P>
<P>
Hearing the speeches of Ningxia deputies, Jiang said Ningxia
has made notable progress in economic development, because local
officials and the masses of people have kept taking as the
guidance Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese
charac implemente the central authorities' political line,
principles and policies, and defined a road of development in
confmity with Ningia's conditions.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he said, the regional Party committees and
governments have always paid attention to correctly handling the
relations between reform, development and stability, and,
proceeding from the characteristics of local ethnic regions, made
special efforts in promoting ethnic unity and social stability,
which created a good social and political environment for leading
multi-ethnical people in all-out effort for economic development.
</P>
<P>
There do exist fairly big gaps between coastal areas in eastern
China and central and western regions, Jiang noted. With a vast
territory and varied conditions nationwide, China cannot achieve
synchronous development and prosperity in different regions.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
