<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls for Faster Development in Central, Western China (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fairly big progress has been made in the work of pooling
efforts to help the needy to become better off and provide 1.22
million locals in Gansu with enough to eat and wear, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
"The facts have once again proved that even if the existing
conditions were unfavorabvldevelopment will still be accelerated
provided that we adhere to Deng Xiaoping's theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics and are guided by the
Party's basic lines, conscientiously carry out the central
authorities' principles and policies, and have formulated a
correct development strategy by combining the theory and basic
line with specific conditions in the region,"Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He acknowledged that Gansu's agricultural basis is still weak,
and the livelihoods of its 3.75 million people are still below the
poverty line; quite a number of state-owned enterprises face
problems in operation; governments at various levels are still in
financial difficulties; and the infrastructure is relatively
backward.
</P>
<P>
He called for a high degree of attention paid to these
difficulties and problems, which should merit the attention from
all sectors so as to enhance people's confidence for further
progress.
</P>
<P>
The central government has set for the relevant policies in
support of central and western China, and will continue to its
aid.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Jiang urged provincial and local governments to
further emancipate their mind, dare to explore, and work in a
down-to-earth way, so as to open up a new situation for Gansu's
development.
</P>
<P>
To accelerate economic development, the central and western
regions should deal with problem of lagging-behind infrastructure,
said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He called on provincial and local governments to do overall
planning with emphasis to be placed on major issues to improve the
infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Jiang voiced his wish that both cadres and the people in
Ningxia and Gansu will do a still better job of reform and
opening, and modernization, and greet the convocation of the 15th
CPC National Congress with concrete deeds and new achievements.
</P>
</TEXT>
