<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Self-Ruled Gaza to Build First Complex </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 1 (Xinhua) -- The construction of a
100-million-U.S.-dollar business and tourism complex in Gaza, the
first of the kind in the Palestinian self-ruled area, was official
launched today, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Organizers of the project said that the project was a vote of
confidence for the peace process, and that it will burst tourism
and business in the Palestinian autonomous areas.
</P>
<P>
The complex includes a Marriot Hotel, a convention center,
offices, restaurants, and a health club.
</P>
<P>
The project is financed jointly by U.S.-based General Resources
Design Group, the Salam International Investment, based in the
Gulf state of Qatar, and the Palestinian National Authority.
</P>
<P>
The complex will have its own infrastructure, including an
independent power plant, waste water treatment facilities, and a
telecommunication center which will serve the general public.
</P>
<P>
Organizers said that the project is scheduled to employ
some 2,000 workers during the construction period, and will
provide 4,000 jobs in related enterprises, and inject more
than 50 million U.S. dollars into the Gaza economy annually.
</P>
</TEXT>
