<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 23 French Policemen Wounded by Malians Expelled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-three French policemen were
wounded -- three seriously -- by a group of 77 Malians who were
expelled from France, when their chartered Boeing jet landed in
the Malian capital Bamako Thursday night, said officials.
</P>
<P>
The police, who escorted the expulsion, were attacked inside
the cabin by some expellees after it touched down on the Bamako
airport, and some other expellees tried to destroy the plane with
any tools at hand.
</P>
<P>
The plane, which belonged to the Air France company and
chartered by the French government, was seriously damaged, said
officials of Air France.
</P>
<P>
The unionists of the Air France have protested what they called
"the inhuman and violent conditions" under which Africans were
expelled from France for years.
</P>
<P>
They said that the expellees were scotch-taped, handcuffed and
sometimes drugged and chloroformed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
