<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top PLA Officer on Army Building (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- The key to advancing the great
cause of building socialism with Chinese characteristics initiated
by Deng Xiaoping is to uphold his theory in this regard and never
waver in adhering to the Party's basic line, said a top Chinese
military leader today.
</P>
<P>
Liu Huaqing, vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission,
made the remark at a group discussion attended by Army deputies to
the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC) now in session in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
He said, "No matter how many obstacles lie ahead, the PLA must
unswervingly advance along the road pointed out by Deng Xiaoping."
</P>
<P>
Liu, who is also a member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China Central
Committee, expressed his approval for Premier Li Peng's
government work report.
</P>
<P>
On army building, Liu said the Chinese People's Liberation Army
will quicken the pace of improving its own quality, noting that
quality improvement has become a basic defence policy for all
major countries in the world since the beginning of the 1990s.
</P>
<P>
To meet changes in the form of war and the pattern of strategy,
the PLA decided quality improvement for the army as an important
guiding principle when formulating its plan for army building
during the Eighth Five-Year Plan period (1991-1995), he said.
</P>
<P>
With the support of the Party Central Committee and the State
Council, new strides have been made in this regard and the PLA has
remarkably improved its quality and defence combat capability,
he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
