<HEADLINE> Top PLA Officer on Army Building (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Liu said, "We should seize rare historical opportunities and
try every possible means to step up army building.
</P>
<P>
"Although it is impossible for the Central Government to
increase defence budget by a large margin, we can still accomplish
a great deal as long as we make meticulous plans and spend the
limited amount of money in key areas with emphasis placed on
efficiency.
</P>
<P>
"It is a pressing and long-term task for the PLA to strengthen
the army through scientific and technological progresses. We
should work in this direction now and in the 21st century. We
should never waver in this regard.
</P>
<P>
"For quality improvement, the PLA must pursue a policy of
maintaining a proper size with great combat readiness, optimize
its organizational structure, give strategic importance to
education and drilling, develop high-tech weapons, develop new
combat theories, and strengthen discipline and administration."
</P>
<P>
Efforts must also be made to strengthen political and
ideological education and improve the quality of soldiers in an
all-round way so as to improve their ability to handle modern
wars, he said.
</P>
<P>
The vice-chairman urged military officers to be better prepared
for China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
On July 1 this year, China will resume the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong and the PLA will have its troops
stationed in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
After the return of Hong Kong to China, "we will firmly
implement the principle of 'one country, two systems', 'Hong Kong
people governing Hong Kong' and 'a high degree of autonomy' to
ensure that Hong Kong maintains its prosperity and stability, he
said
</P>
