<HEADLINE> Algerian President to Meet with Opposition on Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Algerian President Liamine Zeroual
will meet with the country's opposition parties next week to
discuss the legislative elections to be held on May 28 or June 5,
said reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Algerian television said that the meeting will focus on a
report drafted by a working group charged with defining the
make-up of an independent national election commission to be in
charge of supervising the elections.
</P>
<P>
The working group consisted of 29 political parties and a
presidential representative, and was established by the government
in February in coordination with some oppositions.
</P>
<P>
But one of the main opposition parties of the country, the
Front of Socialist Forces, which boycotted previous meetings with
President Zeroual and voted against the constitutional amendment
on November 28, 1996, has not decided whether it will join next
week's meeting or not, reported the Agence France-Presse (AFP).
</P>
