<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- State-owned enterprises must seize
the opportunity to go in for structural readjustment and quicken
their pace in establishing modern enterprise system, so as to
invigorate the State-owned enterprises operating in a loss, said
Tian Jiyun today.
</P>
<P>
In a panel discussion with deputies from southwest China's
Guizhou Province, Tian, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of
the National People's Congress (NPC), said in the NPC's on-going
session that the major task for Guizhou is to overcome poverty and
work hard in the reform of the state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Tian, also a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, deliberated Premier Li
Peng's government work report delivered this morning.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo also joined in a panel discussion with
deputies from Shanghai, China's largest industrial center. He
urged Shanghai enterprises to work in structural readjustment to
comply with market demand and changes at market and develop
economy with special characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Zou Jiahua, also vice-premier of the State Council, addressed
the topic of the gigantic Three Gorges Project during a panel
discussion with deputies from southwestern China's Sichuan, the
most populous province in China. He said the most important thing
for the success of the project is resettlement, and displacement
through development.
</P>
