<HEADLINE> Senior Leaders Join in Panel Group Discussion (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun told legislators from east China's
Shandong Province that the central government attached great
importance to agriculture, when Premier Li Peng said in his
government work report that agriculture will continue to be the
top priority in the country's economic work.
</P>
<P>
Although China has achieved good harvests for two consecutive
years and marked increase made in the farmers' incomes, he said,
the people should by no means feel contented and overestimate the
country's agricultural productivity.
</P>
<P>
"Since the founding of New China in 1949, we have suffered
several major setbacks in grain production. One major reason lies
in a blind optimism and letup following harvests," he recalled.
</P>
<P>
During discussions with legislators from north China's Hebei
Province, Wang Bingqian, vice-chairman of the NPC Standing
Committee, stressed the importance of education and science and
technology.
</P>
<P>
"If we want to seek economic development, we should pay special
attention to science and technology, and to knowledge and talented
personnel," he noted, adding that invigorating the country with
science and education is a correct strategy for China's economic
development.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that apart from increasing state investment,
the government should also encourage various social sectors to
provide more financial support for the development of science and
education.
</P>
<P>
Several other senior officials, including Vice Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen and State Councillor Luo Gan, also
took part in today's panel discussions.  
</P>
