<HEADLINE> Tornadoes Strike Northern Mississippi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 1 (Xinhua) -- One people was killed and at
least four others injured in tornadoes produced by severe
thunderstorms that swept northern Mississippi this morning.
</P>
<P>
Some 15 homes were damaged by the tornadoes that struck about
1:30 a.m. local time in the commutity Randolph, about 30 miles
southwest of Tupelo, Mississippi Emergency Management Agency said.
</P>
<P>
At least four people were hospitalized, including one person
with a broken back.
</P>
<P>
The storms that surged into the area were expected to move into
the Great Lakes states by tonight. Large hail, damaging winds and
up to 2 inches of rain were predicted. 
</P>
