<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- The People's Liberation Army
(PLA) will unswervingly obey the orders of the Party Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
The remark was made today by Zhang Zhen, vice-chairman of the
Central Military Commission, in a group discussion at the on-going
session of the National People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
The general said the PLA must enhance their political
awareness, observe disciplines and have the overall situation in
mind to carry work forward at the behest of Deng Xiaoping,
unswervingly safeguard the authority of Communist Party Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core to advance the great cause
of building socialism with Chinese characteristics initiated by
Deng Xiaoping and push ahead with reform, opening up and the
modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said the theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics put forward by Deng Xiaoping is Marxism in
present-day China. It also represents an inheritance and
development of Mao Zedong Thought.
</P>
<P>
"Under all circumstances, we should arm ourselves with the
theory and use it to understand and deal with contradictions and
problems arising in the modernization drive," he said.
</P>
<P>
The PLA must do its work with the overall situation in mind.
"This is an important component of Deng Xiaoping's theory on army
building in the new period," he said.
</P>
