<HEADLINE> Military Set-up Transforms Into Mill in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 1 (Xinhua) -- A military establishment used
to repair tanks by the former government has been transformed
into a productive enterprise, a report from the Ethiopian News
Agency said today.
</P>
<P>
The newly inaugurated Zuquala steel rolling mill, located at
Debre Zeit town, about 45 kms east of Addis Ababa, has the
capacity to produce 100,000 tons of metal products per annum,
such as reinforced bars of various shapes, plate sections and
angle irons of different sizes.
</P>
<P>
The factory, transformed at a cost of about 7.7 million
Dollars, is expected to enter into full-capacity operation after
six months. It will help supply the now booming construction
industry of the country with 60 to 70 percent of its demand for
raw material. 
</P>
</TEXT>
