<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 18:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Death Toll Rises to 350 in Iranian Quake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 1 (Xinhua) -- The death toll rose to 350 and
some 1,650 others were injured Saturday in an earthquake which hit
northwest Iran Friday afternoon, an official report said today.
</P>
<P>
Governor General of Ardebil Mahmood Ahmadi, was quoted by the
official news agency IRNA as saying that the earthquake inflicted
damage between 40 and 100 percent on 56 villages.
</P>
<P>
According to an earlier report, the quake measuring six
degrees on the Richter scale struck cities of Ardebil and Meshkin
Shahr and their surrounding villages, about 600 kilometers
northwest of the Iranian capital Tehran.
</P>
<P>
Relief teams have been continuing operations to rescue
survivors of the quake which occurred at 16:31 local time (13:01
GMT) Friday.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the tremor, which lasted for about 15
seconds, panicked people and drove them out into the streets.
</P>
<P>
Several aftershocks followed.
</P>
<P>
Iran is earthquake-prone and is rocked by hundreds of tremors
every year, some of which caused widespread damage.
</P>
<P>
This is the second major earthquake within a month. On
February 4, a quake measuring 6.1 degrees on the Richter scale
jolted northern Khorasan province, killing a total of 86 people
and injuring hundreds of others.
</P>
<P>
Over 100 villages suffered varying degrees of destruction,
some totally razed. Over 11,000 houses were damaged, making
thousands of villagers homeless. 
