Nations Special Commission (UNSCOM) on Iraq will also be
discussed during the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Under the U.N. resolution, Iraq is allowed to sell 2 billion
U.S. dollars worth of oil every six months to finance purchases
of food, medicine and other basic necessities for the sanction-hit
people in the country.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has so far submitted 190 trade contracts to the sanctions
committee. However, only eight of the deals have been approved.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has blamed the interference by the U.S. representative in
the committee for the delay. 
