<HEADLINE> China Beats Bosnia 3-0 to Win Dunhill Cup Soccer Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 2 (Xinhua) -- China scored three goals in
the second half to beat Bosnia-Herzegovina 3-0 to claim the title
of the Dunhill Cup soccer championship here on Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
The two sides tied 0-0 in the first half.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, kept unbeaten in all three group matches and
ousted Zimbabwe 3-1 in Friday's semifinals, opened their score
with a 56th-minute goal from 19-year-old substitute Li Jinyu.
</P>
<P>
Two minutes later, Li Jinyu's header shot was blocked away by
Bosnian goalkeeper Dedic Mirsad, but Zhang Xiaorui stroke the
rebounder home to give China a 2-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
China dominated the rest of the play and Hao Haidong scored the
third and last goal for China with a pass from right corner by Ma
Mingyu with 10 minutes left on the clock.
</P>
<P>
Eight teams took part in the inaugural Dunhill Cup soccer
tournament which kicked off on February 21. 
</P>
</TEXT>
