<HEADLINE> Tibetan Chairman Voices Opposition to Dalai's Schemes to Split China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- A top Tibetan official voiced his
strong opposition to Dalai Lama for his activities to split China
today.
</P>
<P>
Gyaincain Norbu, chairman of the Tibetan Autonomous Regional
Government, made the remark at the on-going session of the
National People's Congress, China's legislature, in response to
reports of a planned visit by Dalai Lama to Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The Dalai clique has engaged in activities to split the
motherland and advocate the so-called independence of Tibet in the
world. It has also colluded with the Taiwan authorities, worked
hand in glove and publicly wallowed in the mire with each other.
</P>
<P>
The facts show that the Dalai clique has gone farther on the
road of splitting the motherland, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Tibetan chairman, who is a deputy to the Eighth NPC, noted
that with the support of the people of the entire country, Tibet
has entered a new period of development in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
He said Tibet achieved an economic growth rate of more than 10
percent in 1995 and 1996. The region's GDP reached 6.453 billion
yuan last year while price rises fell from 17 percent in 1995 to
eight percent last year.
</P>
<P>
The loving attention of the central authorities and support
rendered by the people throughout the country have filled the
Tibetan people with enthusiasm and confidence for united efforts
to accelerate the development.
</P>
</TEXT>
