<HEADLINE> Deng's Economic Theories Key to Economic Success: Zhu (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji called on
China's economic circles today to grasp and follow the rich and
profound economic theories of Deng Xiaoping to advance the
country's economic reform.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the call at a group meeting discussing Premier Li
Peng's government work report. The meeting was attended by members
hailing from economic circles of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, a top advisory
body.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng delivered the report at the Fifth Session of the Eighth
National People's Congress on March 1. Members of the top
advisory body attended the session in a non-deputy capacity.
</P>
<P>
After expressing his grief over Deng Xiaoping's death and
calling for uniting more closely around the Party Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at its core, Zhu said the scientific
contents and gist of Deng's economic theories must be
comprehensively and accurately grasped.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping put forward a series of important ideas,
strategies and decisions for economic work, which profoundly
reflect the law of China's socialist economic construction and
development, and have become an important component of his theory
of building socialism with Chinese characteristics, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
"The successes we have made over the last decade and more are
eloquent proof of the greatness, correctness and vitality of Deng
Xiaoping's economic theories," said Zhu, who is also a member of
the Standing Committee of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC)
Central Committee Political Bureau.
</P>
<P>
"His economic theories are foundmental guidelines for us
to develop our socialist economy with Chinese characteristics
and to realize socialist modernization," Zhu said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970302.0066 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng's Economic Theories Key to Economic Success: Zhu (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Last year was the first year for implementing the country's
ninth five-year plan for national economic and social development
and the long-term goals for 2,010, and it is now clear that it's a
good start, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
The national economy has maintained a sustained rapid growth,
reform and opening up further progressed, inflation gone down
noticeably, the macroeconomic situation improved, and people's
living standard, especially farmers', steadily bettered, he said.
</P>
<P>
These achievements have laid a solid foundation for the smooth
return of Hong Kong to the embrace of the motherland, the
convening of the 15th Party Congress, and the accomplishment of
the ninth five-year national plan in an all-round fashion, the
vice-premier said.
</P>
<P>
He said this year's economic work has a clear orientation with
concrete measures. They are:
</P>
<P>
-- Greater attention to be paid to reforming the state sector,
to economic restructuring, and to changing the mode of growth.
</P>
<P>
-- Continued priority to be given to developing agriculture as
the economic base. The grain circulation system should be further
reformed with a view to encouraging farmers to produce more.
</P>
<P>
-- Continued appropriately tight financial and monetary
policies to be pursued. Budgets must be observed rigorously, more
efforts should be made to increase revenue and cut spending,
reform of the financial system should be deepened, and supervision
over financial institutions should be intensified.
</P>
<P>
Twelve National Committee members of the CPPCC spoke at
the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
