<HEADLINE> Chairman of China's Top Advisory Body Highlights Stability </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of China's top advisory
body today urged its members to cherish the hard-won stability
China now enjoys.
</P>
<P>
"We must conscientiously follow Deng Xiaoping's theory of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics, cherish to the
utmost extent the current situation of unity and stability and
solve problems effectively," Li Ruihuan, member of the Standing
Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China,
said when he attended a group discussion, part of the activities
of the ongoing fifth session of the Eighth National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
How to make people rich and the country prosperous is an
issue that many socialist countries have failed to resolve
properly, said Li, who is also chairman of the CPPCC National
Committee.
</P>
<P>
"Our Party scored great achievements but also suffered many
setbacks in this regard and has paid a cost that is not small,
such as the miserable cost of the 'Cultural Revolution'," he said.
</P>
<P>
The big issue was not resolved fundamentally in China until the
third plenum of the 11th CPC Central Committee, when Comrade Deng
Xiaoping initiated the theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics, Li said.
</P>
<P>
"Without Deng Xiaoping's theory, there would not have been such
a prosperous situation in China or a bright and broad future," he
noted.
</P>
<P>
It's the broadest public will and opinion in China to carry
forward this theory and all the comrades that are concerned about
people's interests and about the long-term stability of the
nation, especially leading officials at all levels, must
conscientiously follow Deng Xiaoping's theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, he said.
</P>
<P>
At present, the third generation of the central collective
leadership with Jiang Zemin at the core is united, the whole Party
is united, people of the entire nation are united, and the
country's social and political situation is stable, he said.
</P>
<P>
"This is a fundamental guarantee for us to carry forward our
cause," he said. "Without this, nothing can be achieved."
</P>
<P>
In its history of the past 100 years, China focused on economic
construction only in the last 18 years, according to Li.
</P>
<P>
"We must cherish to the utmost extent and meticulously
safeguard the current situation of unity and stability," he urged.
"We should not say or do anything harmful to unity and to stability."
</P>
<P>
China is hopeful so long as there is a united and stable
situation and Deng Xiaoping's theory is followed, Li said.
</P>
<P>
He said that China's reform, opening-up and modernization drive
have scored achievements recognized by all.
</P>
<P>
However, he added that China is also facing some difficult
problems that must be solved.
</P>
<P>
"First I want to say that it is normal there will be some
difficulties and problems in a process such as establishing a
socialist market economic system," Li said.
</P>
<P>
"And second, earnest effort must be made to solve the
difficulties and problems, or there will be great repercussions,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Li called on the members to offer realistic ideas and ways to
solve the difficulties and problems.  
</P>
</TEXT>
