<HEADLINE> PLC Working Group Discusses Rules of Procedure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The Rules of Procedure working
group under the Provisional Legislative Council (PLC) of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) has started to
formulate a set of rules guiding the operation of the legislature.
</P>
<P>
The 12-member ad hoc group held a closed-door meeting today in
Shenzhen, the Chinese city bordering Hong Kong, to discuss what
rules of procedure should be laid for the provisional legislature
and committees under the PLC.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Selina Chow, convener of the group
said: "while working out these rules, we, first of all, consider
what main tasks the PLC will undertake and what rules of
procedures the PLC will need." She stressed that all these rules
should be in line with the Basic Law and related resolutions by
the Preparatory Committee, which shoulders the responsibility of
establishing the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
According to Chow, the working group today discussed the voting
system and ways of determining motions in the provisional
legislature, the system of committees under the PLC, as well as
internal guidelines for various committees.
</P>
<P>
Set up on February 22 at the PLC plenary meeting, the Rules of
Procedure working team is engaged in working out rules guiding the
operation of the PLC. The team will hold its next meeting in
Shenzhen on March 8 and 9, said Chow.  
</P>
</TEXT>
