<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Non-Communist Parties Not to Function in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- China's non-Communist party
organizations will neither establish branches, nor admit new
members, nor establish ties with political organizations of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) in Hong Kong after
its return to China, said three top non-Communist party leaders
today.
</P>
<P>
The three newly elected non-Communist party chairpersons made
known the policy in response to a question from a Hong Kong
reporter at a press conference today.
</P>
<P>
Chen Siwei, chairman of China Democratic National Construction
Association, said the multi-party cooperation system under the
leadership of the Communist Party of China is the political party
system and part of the political system in China.
</P>
<P>
After the Chinese government resumes the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong, Hong Kong will not practice a
socialist system and the political party system in the interior
will not be introduced into Hong Kong in line with the Basic Law
of HKSAR, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
