<HEADLINE> Ethiopians Celebrate 101st Anniversary of Adwa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian people today
celebrated the 101st anniversary of the Adwa victory over the
Italian invaders.
</P>
<P>
In the capital city of Addis Ababa, the day was marked at the
Menelik Square in the presence of patriots of the anti-colonial
resistance and thousands of residents of Addis Ababa.
</P>
<P>
Dawit Yohannes, Speaker of the House of People's
Representatives, laid a wreath on the Menelik Monument.
</P>
<P>
A 106-year-old patriot, Ferede Zerfu, said that Ethiopian
sovereignity and independence was preserved thanks to the sacrifice
of the dear sons and daughters of the nation. The present generation
has the responsibility to preserving that legacy, he added.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here, the day was also observed
throughout the nation including northern town of Adwa.
</P>
<P>
On March 1, 1896, Ethiopian soldiers led by Emperor Menelik ii
defeated 15,000 well-equipped Italian invaders at Adwa in northern
Ethiopia. The famous battle of Adwa forced the Italian aggressors
to recognize Ethiopia as a sovereign independent state. Ethiopia
celebrates the adwa victory day every year on March 2.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
