<HEADLINE> Nigeria Prepares for Site of All-Africa Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The Kaduna International Trade Fair
Complex, the site for the Seventh All-Africa Trade Fair scheduled
for March 29, has nearly been completed, officials said today.
</P>
<P>
Dauda Dau, chairman of the technical committee of the
organizing committee, said construction workers are currently
busy with roofing, cladding and internal partition and so on.
</P>
<P>
A contractor said they are "almost through with utilities like
water, electricity and telecommunications."
</P>
<P>
The Petroleum Trust Fund of Nigeria, which financed the trade
fair complex expansion work, had set February 28 as the deadline for
the construction work, but there have been some delays due to
financial and other problems.
</P>
<P>
There would be no fear that the trade fair, jointly organized
by the Organization of African Unity and African Economic
Community, would be cancelled, postponed or have its venue
changed, said Nigeria's official newspaper, the New Nigerian.
</P>
<P>
It added that exhibitors are already rushing to secure spaces
for "the biggest commercial exhibition in Africa in the 20th
century."
</P>
<P>
Dau said 10,000 square meters of indoor exhibition space and
40,000 square meters of outdoor space would be available at the
fair ground.
</P>
<P>
The complex would be thrown open later this week for
businesses to set up their pavilions, which must be ready on or
before March 26. 
</P>
</TEXT>
