<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UAE Calls for Establishment of Palestinian State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates (UAE)
today called for the establishment of a Palestinian state in the
Middle East region, the UAE's official news agency WAM reported.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with the Visiting former U.S. senator George
Mitcheele this morning, the UAE Deputy Prime Minister Sheikh
Sultan bin Zayed Al Nahyan underlined the necessity to give the
Palestinians legal rights and called for the establishment of an
independent Palestinian state on the Palestinian land, WAM said.
</P>
<P>
The call comes after a decision by the Israeli government on
February 26 to build thousands of new Jewish homes in the now
undeveloped Har Homa area on the southern edge of East Jerusalem,
which has sparked world criticism.
</P>
<P>
The deputy prime minister reiterated his country's condemnation
against the Israeli settlement policy, saying the policy did not
serve peace in the Middle East region and Israel should stop such
policy and abide by the peace agreements signed between the
Palestinians and Israel.
</P>
<P>
The UAE's Minister of State for Foreign Affairs Sheikh Hamdan
bin Zayed Al Nahyan also blasted the Israeli policy on Saturday,
Saying it "is destroying peace opportunities and disturbing the
security and stability in the Middle East region".
</P>
<P>
Referring to the Middle East peace process, the deputy prime
minister told Mitcheele that more international efforts should be
made for the achievement of a comprehensive and just peace in
the region.
</P>
<P>
He said the efforts should focus on imposing more pressure on
Israel until it returns to the peace track for the stability
in the region, WAM said.
</P>
<P>
Mitcheele, who has been the advisor of the U.S. President Bill
Clinton for the Northern Ireland Affairs, is paying a
two-day Private visit to the UAE and he will leave here Monday, an
official from the U.S. embassy in the UAE said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
