<HEADLINE> Taiwan Increasing Investment in China's inland Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Taiwan's planned investment in the
China's inland areas in January is reported to have surpassed 96
million US dollars, an increase of 37 percent over the same month
of 1996, according to recent reports.
</P>
<P>
The cultural similarities and shared origins have helped
increase the interest of the people of Taiwan in investing in the
mainland, especially in coastal areas and those with developed
transport, such as Guangdong, Jiangsu, and Shandong provinces.
</P>
<P>
Of the investment, more than 41 million US dollars are marked
for Guangdong Province, 23 million for Jiangsu, and 15 million US
dollars for Shandong, up 254 percent, 27 percent, and 293 percent
respectively from the same period of 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
