<HEADLINE> U.S.A Beats Australia 3-1 in Women's Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Olympic champions the United
States defeated Australia 3-1 in the second game of a three-match
international women's soccer series in Bathurst of Australia on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Americans poured all their three goals in the second-half
with Justi Baumgardt scoring in the 52nd minute, Kristine Lilly in
the 66th and Brandi Chastain in the 74th.
</P>
<P>
Australia's consolation goal by Sunni Hughes came in the
90th-minute.
</P>
<P>
The United States won the first game of the series 4-0 on
Friday in Melbourne and the final game is to be played for next
Wednesday in Canberra. 
</P>
