<HEADLINE> East China City to Expand Tourism in Outlying Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Nanjing, a city known for its
history, in east China's Jiangsu Province, established a tourism
coordinating association today to develop tourism in the areas
around the city.
</P>
<P>
The association has the cities of Nanjing, Hefei, Nanchang,
Yangzhou, Zhenjiang, Huangshan, Ma'anshan, Liuan, Chuzhou,
Chaozhou, Anqing, Jiujiang and Jingdezhen, most of which are on
the border with Jiangsu, Anhui, and Jiangxi provinces, as members.
</P>
<P>
With their natural conditions and rich tourist resources, the
cities have formed tourist areas around Nanjing that include the
historical spots of Nanchang, Yangzhou and Zhenjiang, and some
scenic spots, such as Huangshan and Lushan mountains.
</P>
<P>
The cities will increase information exchanges on tourism,
improve advertising and sales promotion, and make joint efforts to
open regional tourist lines and build regional tourist
organizations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
