<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Deputies, CPPCC Members Confident in HK's Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese legislators and government
advisors maintained that the future of Hong Kong will be more
splendid.
</P>
<P>
The return of Hong Kong to the motherland has been a hot topic
among deputies to the Fifth Session of the Eighth National
People's Congress (NPC) and members of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) National Committee, both
of which are in session here.
</P>
<P>
The return of Hong Kong will wash off the disgrace of the
Chinese nation that lasted 100 years and is a successful
application of the principle of "one country, two systems"
initiated by Deng Xiaoping, the deputies and members said.
</P>
<P>
They said that they are fully confident in Hong Kong's return.
</P>
<P>
Ling Qing, vice-chairman of the Foreign Affairs Committee of
the CPPCC National Committee, expressed his excitedness about Hong
Kong's return in some 120 days in a poem in praise of the return
of Hong Kong, which shakes off China's national shame as the
country has taken off.
</P>
<P>
Tsui Sze-man, an 83-year-old CPPCC member from Hong Kong, said
that many Hong Kong residents, who left to reside overseas
earlier, have returned, and this epitomized the people's
confidence in the future of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He Guoqiang, a NPC deputy and acting governor of eastern Fujian
Province, said that Hong Kong's return will consolidate its
economic links with the interior area.
</P>
<P>
Leading Chinese officials also talked of the Hong Kong issue
extensively in recent days.
</P>
<P>
Joining CPPCC members representing Hong Kong and Macao,
President Jiang Zemin said that one big event this year is China's
resumption of the exercise of its sovereignty over Hong Kong and
bringing Hong Kong to a more prosperous and stable future in
accordance with the principle of "one country, two systems", "Hong
Kong people governing Hong Kong" and "a high degree of autonomy".
</P>
<P>
"We must carry forward at the behest of Deng Xiaoping and do a
good job with matters related to Hong Kong and Macao," Jiang
noted.
</P>
<P>
When he was delivering a work report Saturday, Premier Li Peng
used the word "will" three times to pledge the resolve of his
government to ensure a smooth transfer of Hong Kong and to
maintain the prosperity and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
"The policy of 'one country, two systems' will be crowned with
success, and Hong Kong will maintain long-term prosperity and
stability and its future will surely be even brighter," he said.
</P>
<P>
A fairly lengthy part of the CPPCC National Committee's work
report also covers the issue of Hong Kong's return, saying that
one major task of the advisory body this year is to "actively
support and assist the Central Government in the work concerning
the transfer of government in Hong Kong and the celebration of the
return of Hong Kong to the motherland".
</P>
<P>
Since the first chief executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region and the Provisional Legislative Council have
been elected and the leading officials of the government of the
Hong Kong SAR have been appointed by the Central Government,
people have every reason to believe that Hong Kong's future is
bright and its tomorrow will be more splendid. 
</P>
</TEXT>
