<DOCNO> XIE19970302.0115 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Civilian Flights to Gulu Resume </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Civilian flights to the northern
city of Gulu, which was suspended last week, resumed on Feruary
28, the New Vision reported today.
</P>
<P>
Shaban Bantariza, a Gulu-based Public Relation Officer of the
Second Division of the Ugandan Army, said the Gulu airport was
closed for security reasons. However, he did not elaborate.
</P>
<P>
Amama Mbabazi, the Ugandan State Minister for Defence, said
last Tuesday that the Gulu Airport was closed because of air
raids of the cities of Moyo and Arua by Sudanese aircrafts
in mid-February.
</P>
<P>
Brigadier Joram Mugume, the Chief of Cambat Operation of the
Uganda Army, said on February 27 that the situation in northern
Uganda was normal, and the closure of the airport was a
precotious measure.
</P>
<P>
''We were bombed... We don't want many aircrafts at the Gulu
airport,'' he said. enditem

