<HEADLINE> Middle East Oil, Gas Conference Opens in UAE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, March 2 (Xinhua) -- More than 500 representatives
from 50 countries gathered here to attend the 5th Annual Middle
East Petroleum and Gas (MPGC) conference, which opened today.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day gathering on March 2-4, the participants
will discuss strategic trends and new project opportunities in the
oil and gas industries in the Middle East region.
</P>
<P>
Dr. F. Fesharaki, chairman of the MPGC conference, said that
the participants will discuss a future vision for oil pricing and
fluctuation, oil markets and liquefied natural gas
industrialization in Central Asia, Russia and the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
The conference was held within the framework of of the Middle
East Oil Week, which started Saturday and will conclude on March 6.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the MPGC conference, three other specialized
conferences will also be held as part of the Middle East Oil Week.
</P>
<P>
The three conferences are the Conference of Oil Strategies in
the Middle East, Conference on Liquefied Petroleum Gas and
Conference on Trading Ship Fuels. 
