<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Visit China '97  (22) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Following is an explanation for
Visit China '97, which is mentioned by Chinese Premier Li Peng
in his government work report to the Fifth Session of the Eighth
National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
To promote China's rich tourism resources and intrduce more
tourism products onto overseas markets, China National Tourism
Administration (CNTA) designated this year as Visit China '97.
</P>
<P>
The program is expected to further promote the development of
China's travel and civil aviation industries.
</P>
<P>
During Visit China '97, China's tourism industry will launch 16
special travel routes and 48 festivals focusing on themes of
natural scenery, places of historical interest, folk customs,
vacationing, and special-theme travels.
</P>
<P>
As another important part of the program, a nationwide drive
to improve services will be launched in more
than 60 tourist cities.  
