<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Nanjiang (Southern Xinjiang) Rail Line (11) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Following is a brief introduction
on the Nanjiang Railway line, a national key project mentioned in
Chinese Premier Li Peng's government work report to the Fifth
Session of the Eighth National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
The 1,470-km railway is located in northwest China's Xinjiang
Uygur Autonomous Region. It extends from Turpan on the
Lanzhou-Xinjiang line at the east end to Kashi in southern
Xinjiang at the west end. The 495-km eastern section from Turpan
to Korla went into service in 1984.
</P>
<P>
The western section, from Korla to Kashi via Aksu, started
construction in September of 1996 as a major mational project in
the 1996-2000 period. The 975-section runs through four
prefectures in the region, and will have a short-term carrying
capacity of five million tons, and a long-term capacity of 15
million tons each year.
</P>
<P>
The project is estimated to cost 5.9 billion yuan, and will go
into operation in three and a half years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
