<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Third-Phase Construction of Baosteel (12) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Following is a brief introduction
to the third-phase construction of Shanghai Baoshan Iron and Steel
Complex, a national key project mentioned in Chinese Premier Li
Peng's government work report to the Fifth Session of the Eight
National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Baoshan Iron and Steel Complex (Baosteel), a major
steel producer in China, has started its third-phase construction,
with the key project of the phase, a hot-rolling mill, launched
last October.
</P>
<P>
The third-phase expansion will include 12 projects. It will
boost Baosteel's annual production capacity to 11 million tons of
steel, a condition allowing the firm to become one of 500 largest
businesses in the world.
</P>
<P>
Baosteel, located on the northeastern outskirts of Shanghai, is
a large modern iron and steel complex built up initially with
imported equipment and technology. Construction of the complex
started in December of 1978, and the first and second phases of
its construction were completed in 1985 and 1991 respectively.
</P>
</TEXT>
