<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Yangcheng Pithead Power Plant (13) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Following is a brief introduction
to the Yangcheng Power Plant, a national key project mentioned in
Chinese Premier Li Peng's government work report to the Fifth
Session of the Eighth National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
Yangcheng Pithead Power Plant, the world's biggest burning
anthracite and China's first Sino-US jointly-run power plant,
started construction on January 28 in Yangcheng city in north
China's Shanxi province. Its total investment is estimated at 13.2
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The plant, with six 350,000-kilowatt sets, will have an
installed capacity of 2.1 million kw. With power generated here
transmitted to east China's Jiangsu province via a 755-km
500-kilovolt line, the plant will be able to provide more than 10
billion kwh of electricity to Jiangsu each year.
</P>
<P>
Yangcheng International Power Co., a joint venture of five
Chinese companies and an American partner, is in charge of loan
repayment as well as the plant's construction and operation.
</P>
</TEXT>
