<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Shule River Project  (14) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Following is a brief introduction
to Shule River Project, a key national project mentioned in
Chinese Premier Li Peng's government work report to the Fifth
Session of the Eighth National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
The Shule River project is a super-big agricultural development
scheme with World Bank loans in northwest China's Gansu province.
</P>
<P>
The 2.697 billion yuan project, also called the Gansu Corridor
project, was launched in the first half of 1996 and is scheduled
to be completed in ten years.
</P>
<P>
The project combines water conservancy and irrigation,
resettlement of local residents, and development of the
agricultural sector in the area.
</P>
<P>
It is of great significance to the stable development of the
sector, and alleviation of grain shortage in Gansu.  
</P>
