<DOCNO> XIE19970302.0131 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Adequate Housing Project (17) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Following is an explanation of the
Adequate Housing Project, a term mentioned in Premier Li Peng's
government work report to the Fifth Session of the Eighth National
People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
The project launched by the Chinese government in 1994 aims to
increase the supply of housing in cities and towns, promote
housing reform, and realize the goal of providing eight sq m of
housing floor space for each urban resident on average by the end
of the century.
</P>
<P>
According to the project, 150 million sq m of housing will be
built to solve the housing problem for medium- and low-income
families between 1995 and 2000, and a housing supply system will
be gradually established.
</P>
<P>
The project is being carried out in more than 80 cities across
China. By October of 1996, the state had invested 37.5 billion
yuan in the project, building 43.59 million sq m of housing.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970302.0132 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: System of Provincial Governors Assuming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Following is an explanation of the
system of provincial governors assuming responsibility for the
"rice bag," a term mentioned in Chinese Premier Li Peng's
government work report to the Fifth Session of the Eighth National
People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
To ensure stable market supply of grain, the central government
requires that the government heads of provinces, autonomous
regions and centrally-administered municipalities assume the
responsibility of maintaining grain supplies for their respective
areas.
</P>
<P>
In detail, a governor must see to it that his province:
</P>
<P>
- Keeps a stable area of grain fields and a grain reserve level
meeting demand and increase grain yield;
</P>
<P>
- Fulfils the grain purchase target, and grain and oil reserve
plan set by the central government, and local grain purchase
plans;
</P>
<P>
- Establishes a local risk fund for grain reserve;
</P>
<P>
- Meets the target for inter-province grain flow target set by
the central government if the province is a major grain producer,
or fulfils the target of importing grain or buying grain from
other provinces if the province is not self-sufficient in grain
supply.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
