<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Seed Project  (20) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Following is an explanation for
the seed project, which was mentioned by Chinese Premier Li Peng
in his government work report delivered at the Fifth Session of
the Eighth National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
The project refers to the building of production bases for
wheat, corn, rice, cotton, oil crops and vegetable seeds. The
project aims to build up an annual capacity to process five
billion kg of fine seeds by the year 2000 to allow fine seeds to
account for 95 percent of all seeds used by then.
</P>
<P>
The project, initiated during the Ninth Five-Year Plan period
(1996-2000), includes the five systems of breeding, production and
reproduction, processing and packaging, marketing of the seeds,
and macro management.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
