<DOCNO> XIE19970302.0137 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Loans Turned from Fiscal Allocations (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Following is an explanation to a
policy term on turning fiscal allocations into loans mentioned in
Chinese Premier Li Peng's government work report to the Fifth
Session of the Eighth National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
Qualified Chinese enterprises in some selected areas were
allowed to turn the outstanding principle and interest of loans
for budgeted basic constructions, which are turned from fiscal
allocations between 1979 and 1988, into capital funds, according
to a three-ministry decision approved by the State Council.
</P>
<P>
The policy was limited to two enterprises of cities selected to
improve the capital structure on a trial basis, to cities selected
for experiment with comprehensive reforms, to cities designated by
the State Council to establish a modern enterprise system, and to
the leading enterprises of some designated conglomerates and their
subsidiaries or stake-controlling enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
