<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Nationwide Fitness Campaign (7) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Following is a brief explanation
for the term "nationwide fitness campaign" mentioned by Premier Li
Peng in his government work report to the Fifth Session of the
Eighth National People's Congress:
</P>
<P>
The campaign was launched in 1995 according to a nationwide
physical health enhancement plan formulated by the State Physical
Culture and Sports Commission in 1993 and approved by Premier Li
Peng in June, 1995.
</P>
<P>
The plan, which targets the entire people with an emphasis on
youth and children, is intended to effect a marked improvement for
the general health of the people, and create better conditions for
physical exercises and sports activities of the masses.
</P>
<P>
The "nationwide fitness campaign" is divided into two phases,
and will cover a time span of 15 years (1995-2010).
</P>
<P>
The central authorities have included the "nationwide fitness
plan" in the country's overall plan for national economic
development and social progress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
