<DOCNO> XIE19970302.0144 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: "To Grasp with Both Hands And with Equal Emphasis"(8) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- In his government work report to
the Fifth Session of the Eighth National People's Congress,
Premier Li Peng used the expression of "to grasp with both hands
and with equal emphasis." Following is a brief explanation of the
expression.
</P>
<P>
"To grasp with both hands" means to seize two links at the same
time. One is the material progress, the other is the ethical and
cultural progress. "To grasp with equal emphasis" refers to
attaching equal emphasis to the promotion of the socialist
material progress and of the socialist ethical and cultural
progress, and that the material progress should not be pursued at
the expense of the ethical and cultural progress.
</P>
<P>
Generally speaking, the material progress refers to the
improvement of the people's material life, while the ethical and
cultural progress relies on the advancement of people's wisdom and
morality.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping once said: "The socialist ethical and cultural
progress not only refers to education, science, and culture, but
also includes the Communist ideology, ideals, beliefs, morality,
and discipline, the revolutionary stand and principles, and the
comradeship between the people."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
