<DOCNO> XIE19970302.0145 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Beijing-Kowloon Railway (9) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Following is a brief introduction
to the Beijing-Kowloon Railway, a national key project mentioned
in Chinese Premier Li Peng's government work report to the Fifth
Session of the Eighth National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-Kowloon Railway is the largest ever railway project
in China costing a total of about 40 billion yuan. It is the
country's third trunk rail link from the north to the south after
the Beijing-Guangzhou and the Beijing-Shanghai lines.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the 2,553-km line, running through nine
provinces and municipalities, started at the beginning of 1993.
The line went into operation on September 1, 1996.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-Kowloon Railway has greatly eased strains on the
nation's north-south transportation.
</P>
<P>
It is playing an important role in accelerating the opening-up
pace and economic development in China's coastal, eastern and
middle regions, alleviating poverty in areas along the line, and
promoting prosperity and stability in Hong Kong and Macao.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
