<HEADLINE> Sugiyama Upsets Pierce in Federation Cup Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Ai Sugiyama upset France's Mary
Pierce 7-5, 6-7 (7-9), 6-4 Sunday and pulled one point back for
Japan, keeping her team's Federation Cup hopes still alive.
</P>
<P>
France led 2-1 with two matches remaining. France's Nathalie
Tauziat will face Naoko Sawamatsu in another singles and then a
doubles match.
</P>
<P>
France had taken a 2-0 lead Saturday with victories by Pierce
over Sawamatsu and Tauziat over Sugiyama.
</P>
<P>
Sugiyama, ranked 29th on the WTA tour, ran up to a 5-1 lead and
then blundered through three games in which she won only two
points.
</P>
<P>
But with No. 12 Pierce serving at 4-5 to stay in the match,
Sugiyama scored her seventh break of the three-hour ten-minute
battle, cashing in her fifth match point when Pierce hit a
backhand wide.
</P>
<P>
Sugiyama took limelight at the Atlanta Olympic Games, beating
world top 10 players including Jana Novotna and Anke Huber and
Martina Hingis.
</P>
<P>
The winners of the France-Japan tie advance to the World Group
one semi-finals against the winners between Belgium and Spain.
</P>
</TEXT>
