<HEADLINE> Clinic Opened in Sri Lanka to Treat Cancer Patients </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan Cancer Society
(SLCS) has inaugurated a free clinic in Colombo to identify and
treat all types of cancer.
</P>
<P>
The clinic, called "All Ailment Clinic", is opened on second
Sundays of very month at the head office of the SLCS in Colombo.
</P>
<P>
According to the SLCS today, it has been functioning as a
volunteer organization from 1948 with providing accommodation
facilities for cancer patients, training public to prevent cancer
and conducting awareness programs for people as its main
functions.
</P>
<P>
Anyone irrespective of sex and age can attend this clinic, the
survey added.
</P>
<P>
In a latest survey by the SLCS, about 10,000 Sri Lankans are
suffering from mouth and breast cancer. 
