<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Urges Restoration of Traditional Ties in Eastern </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian President Petar Stoyanov
said here today that time has come for Eastern European countries
to restore their traditional ties of friendship.
</P>
<P>
Stoyanov made the remarks at a news conference after talks with
Czech President Vaclav Havel.
</P>
<P>
He said all East European nations turned their eyes to Western
neighbors after the demolition of the Berlin Wall and now time has
come for them to restore the friendly ties that had traditionally
bound them together.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Prague, the second leg of his current East
European tour, Stoyanov also met with Chairman of the Czech Senate
Petr Pithart, Chairman of the Chamber of Deputies Milos Zeman and
Foreign Minister Josef Zielenice.
</P>
<P>
They discussed European integration, bilateral relations and
other issues.
</P>
<P>
Stoyanov had visited Poland before flying to Prague. He left
for Hungary earlier today. 
</P>
