<HEADLINE> Pakistan Government Gives Grant for Quake Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistani government will
provide a grant of 10 million rupees (about 250,000 U.S. dollars)
for the rehabilitation and relief of earthquake victims in
Baluchistan province.
</P>
<P>
This was announced on Saturday by Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif
when he visited Hernai in Sibi district, the worst affected area
of the province.
</P>
<P>
According to official figure, 38 people were killed and dozens
injured in Hernai in the earthquake which totally caused at least
49 people dead and about 125 injured.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake, which measured 6.3 and 7.3 on the Richter scale
and hit Quetta valley and other parts of northern Baluchistan
province early Friday, was one of the worst in 62 years.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the earthquake was 140 kilometers east of
Baluchistan's capital city of Quetta and it was felt in most of
the province and some parts of Sindh province.  
