<HEADLINE> Armed Group Kills 13 Colombians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen people were
killed by an armed group that raided the Vegachi and Yali
communities in the northwestern Colombian department of Antioquia,
police said today.
</P>
<P>
Ten men on board two vehicles rounded up the Vegachi residents
in the main square, made a harangue against the guerrillas, and
forced ten of the residents to follow them, police said.
</P>
<P>
They recovered the bodies of nine men, 18 to 47 years old,
killed by the unidentified assailants.
</P>
<P>
The same group carried away five other residents of Vegachi to
an unknown destination.
</P>
<P>
The government has offered a 92,000-U.S.dollar reward for the
capture of the killers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
