<HEADLINE> Thailand to Call on Cambodia to Relax Timber Ban </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Thailand will urge Phnom Penh to
relax its ban on timer exports, according to a Thai National
Security Council (NSC) source.
</P>
<P>
The NSC Saturday agreed to the Thai Foreign Ministry holding
talks with the Cambodian side in an effort to find ways to help
Thai log importers affected by the ban, the source was quoted
today by local press as saying.
</P>
<P>
It will suggest that both countries draw up measures to allow
legal log trading in future, as well as to tighten inspections to
make sure that such logs were legally cut.
</P>
<P>
The source said this was designed to counter criticisms that
Thailand supported illegal logging and log smuggling, the source
said.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia banned timber exports on December 31, 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
