<HEADLINE> Economic, Financial Reports Delivered at NPC Session (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese parliament, which
convened its annual session Saturday, today heard reports on the
country's economic and financial performances last year and plans
for its year.
</P>
<P>
Entrusted by the State Council, Chen Jinhua, minister in charge
of the State Planning Commission, made a report on the
implementation of the 1996 Plan for National Economic and Social
Development and on the Draft 1997 Plan for National Economic and
Social Development, and Liu Zhongli, minister of finance, made a
report on the Implementation of the Central and Local Budgets for
1996 and on the Draft Central and Local Budgets for 1997.
</P>
<P>
Party and government leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi,
Zhu Rongji, Liu Huaqing Rong Yiren attended the second plenary
meeting of the Fifth Session of the Eighth National People's
Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
In his report on Implementation of the 1996 Plan for National
Economic and Social Development and on the Draft 1997 Plan for
National Economic and Social development, Chen Jinhua said China
achieved its goal for macroeconomic control and met the main
targets for national economy and social development in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The national economy scored a sustained and rapid growth last
year, while inflation was effectively curbed, Chen said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China met the goal that price rise should be
lower than the economic growth rate in the first year of the Ninth
Five-Year Plan (1996-2000).
</P>
<P>
Statistics show the retail prices nationwides rose 6.1 percent
last year, remarkably lower the initial target of some 10 percent
and eight percentage points lower than the increase last year; the
GDP reached 6779.5 billion yuan, an increase of 9.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
He acknowledged that main tasks in 1997 include: continuing to
strengthen the position of agriculture as the foundation of the
economy and develop all the sectors of the rural economy;
reinvigorating state-owned enterprises and maintaining an
appropriate industrial growth; vigorously working to optimize the
investment structure; scaling down price rises; making better use
of overseas funds; maintaining financial stability; developing
science, technology and education; continuing to improve the
living standards of the people.
</P>
<P>
In the report on the Implementation of the Central and Local
Budgets for 1996 and on the Draft Central and Local Budgets for
1997, Finance Minister Liu Zhongli told deputies that notable
results were achieved last year in the government's macroeconomic
control endeavors.
</P>
</TEXT>
