<HEADLINE> Effective Measures Needed to Cut Farmers' Burden: Legislators </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Deputies to the Chinese
legislature, the National People's Congress, are call for
effective measures to reduce the financial burden of farmers.
</P>
<P>
It is imperative to cut the financial burden of farmers and
effective measures should be taken, deputies from central China's
Hubei Province said at a group discussion reviewing a government
work report Premier Li Peng delivered at the Fifth Session of the
Eighth NPC Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Zeng Shimin, an official with the agriculture office of
the Hubei provincial government, said that the issue of farmers'
burden can be resolved so long as measures are taken.
</P>
<P>
He said Hubei has established a responsibility system
obliging officials to take measures to reduce farmers' burden.
</P>
<P>
Hubei has taken resolute measures to eliminate unreasonable fees
and return to farmers money collected unreasonably, he said.
</P>
<P>
To date, more than 900 kinds of charges have been eliminated
and over 60 million yuan in illegal fee collections returned to
farmers, he added.
</P>
<P>
Law and rule violations have also been investigated, Zeng said.
</P>
<P>
He also said that measures have been taken to wipe out
rampant fund raising and forced buying of insurance.
</P>
<P>
"The once runaway situation of raising fund illegally and
collecting fees arbitrarily has been brought under control," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Jia Zhijie, secretary of Hubei provincial Party committee, said
that whenever the enthusiasm of farmers is hurt, agriculture will
be affected.
</P>
<P>
He contributed Hubei's record grain output last year, at 24.844
million tons, partly to the effort to protect farmers' enthusiasm.
</P>
<P>
"The work to reduce farmers' burden should never be slackened,"
he noted.
</P>
<P>
"Only when agricultural production grows steadily can there be
a sustained, rapid and healthy development of the entire
provincial economy," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
