<HEADLINE> Economic, Financial Reports Delivered at NPC Session (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The financial and banking situation was stable, said Liu, with
the exchange rate for the RMB remaining stable and and foreign
exchange reserves increasing considerably.
</P>
<P>
The minister affirmed that the central and local budgets were
implemented "fairly satisfactorily" last year, as preliminary
statistics show that total state revenue in 1996 came to 736.661
billion yuan, 107.2 percent of the budgeted figure, and an
increase of 112.441 yuan or 18 percent over the 1995 figure.
</P>
<P>
Total state expenditures amounted to 791.438 billion yuan,
105.7 percent of the budgeted figures, and an increase of 109.066
billion yuan or 16 percent over the 1995 figure. Deficit stood at
54.777 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
He went on to note that in 1997, the government will continue
to follow a relatively stringent financial policy, tighten the
collection and administration of taxation, sustain relatively
rapid growth in revenue, keep expenditures within the limits of
revenue, control total expenditures and optimize their structure,
guarantee key expenditures, continue to cut the deficit, control
the scale of debts, vigorously rectify the financial and economic
order and continue to deepen the reform of finance and taxation.
</P>
<P>
The planned revenues and expenditures for 1997 total 839.794
and 896.794 billion yuan respectively, rising 14 and 13.3 percent
respectively over the 1996 figures, and the deficit is targeted at
57 billion yuan, Liu said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, presided over by Tian Jiyun, an executive chairman
of the session and vice-chairman of the NPC Standing Committee,
was attended by a total of 2,734 deputies today.  
</P>
