<HEADLINE> Veteran Skiier Wins Freestyle Skiing Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 1 (Xinhua) -- American veteran Ian Edmondson won
his first major title in 15 years when he took the title of the
men's freestyle skiing acro-ski at Meiringen, Switzerland, on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Edmondson, 40, scored 26.75 points, beat defending champion
Fabrice Becker of France to the second place at 26.45.
</P>
<P>
Edmondson, who returned to competitions in 1993 after a 10-year
retirement, finished second to Becker in February at the World
Championships at Nagano, Japan.
</P>
<P>
In the women's acro-ski event, Elena Batalova of Russia took
the title, followed by her compatriots Oksana Kushenko and Natalia
Razumovskaia in the second and third places respectively.
</P>
<P>
Batalova earned 26.25 points, world champion kushenko was
second in 25.70. 
</P>
