<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Special Education in Inner Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HUHHOT, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Han Dan, a pretty 14-year-old,
didn't hesitate when asked to recite a classical poem by Li Bai,
the great Chinese romantic poet, for visitors.
</P>
<P>
Han was one of an unusual group of retarded students in the
Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, whose IQs were raised to nearly
45 from their original 0 just four years ago.
</P>
<P>
According to recent statistics, the autonomous regions has 17
schools for local children with disabilities, and 60 special
classes in ordinary primary schools for the same type of
children. Of 14,000 children who have serious eyesight, hearing,
language, or learning disabilities, more than 7,900 are enrolled
in schools, where they not only get a basic education similar to
that of ordinary students, but also learn practical skills like
knitting, planting, music, and arts and crafts.
</P>
<P>
Paintings by local blind children have been exhibited in the
China Art Gallery in Beijing, and some woodcuts produced by
children with speech and hearing impediments have even been shown
in Japan and Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
However, problems still exist in education because of a
shortage of funds and qualified teachers. So, the autonomous
region is calling for support from local authorities and from
individuals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970302.0199 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belgium Leads Spain 2-0 in Federation Cup Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Els Callens and Sabine Appelmans
upset Spain with two singles victories and gave Belgium a
surprising 2-0 lead on Saturday at the Federation Cup tennis in
Sprimont, Belgium.
</P>
<P>
Callens, a late replacement for the injured Dominique Van
Roost, steadily rode a single break of serve to upset
fourth-ranked Arantxa Sanchez Vicario 6-3, 7-6 (7-4).
</P>
<P>
Appelmans, ranked 19th in the world, struggled against Maria
Luisa Serna, listed 64 places lower, but survived 6-1, 4-6, 6-3 to
down the 18-year-old Spanish new face in the Cup.
</P>
<P>
Reverse singles and a concluding doubles are set for Sunday in
the World Group 1 first-round matchup, but Belgium only needs one
win to clinch the victory.
</P>
<P>
Both Spain and Belgium were spoiled by injuries to their No. 2
players.
</P>
<P>
Spain's Conchita Martinez, ranked fifth in the world, did not
even make the trip to Belgium while Van Roost pulled out of her
match on Friday because of a stomach muscle injury that already
contributed to her loss in the quarter-finals of the Australian
Open.
</P>
<P>
The winners of the weekend match plays either France or Japan
in the semi-finals slated for July 12-13. 
</P>
</TEXT>
