<HEADLINE> H Share to Finance Shenzhen Expressway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen Expressway Co Ltd in
Guangdong Province will issue 650 million H shares in mid-March to
build an expressway linking Shenzhen Airport and He'ao, according
to today's "Business Weekly."
</P>
<P>
The company hoped to raise 1.2-1.4 billion yuan (144 to 168
million dollars) for the 44.3 km expressway which is expected to
be completed in June 1999.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen Expressway is the second highway enterprise listed
on the Hong Kong Stock Exchanges. Anhui Expressway Co Ltd in Hong
Kong was listed at the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
The stock market will become a new source for foreign
investment to alleviate the fund shortage and facilitate the
building of the nation's highways, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The Hu-Ning (Shanghai-Nanjing) Expressway Co Ltd, Hu-Hang-Yong
(Shanghai-Hangzhou-Ningbo) Expressway Co Ltd, and the Cheng-Yu
(Chengdu-Chongqing) Expressway Co Ltd are expected to be listed in
Hong Kong this year.
</P>
<P>
Another two enterprises -- Hanna Expressway Co Ltd and the
Ganbei Expressway Co in Jiangxi Province -- will be approved to
float B Shares at an appropriate time by the securities
authorities, it said.
</P>
<P>
China plans to build 6,500 kilometers of highways during the
1996-2000 period, needing some 65 billion U.S. dollars, 15-24 per
cent of which will be a capital shortfall.  
</P>
</TEXT>
