<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Intensify Restructuring Efforts: Minister (7) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In this regard, China will vigorously work to develop
information services, and, in particular, telecommunications,
software and various consultancy services.
</P>
<P>
In the new year, the government will work hard to develop
industries using high and new technologies such as bioengineering,
astronautics, new materials and alternative energy sources.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, the demand for housing among urban
dwellers will continue to grow for a rather long period of time to
come.
</P>
<P>
The central government will create the necessary conditions and
adopt comprehensive supporting measures to guide the urban housing
industry to sound development.
</P>
<P>
He said China will also accelerate urban housing reform, fully
implement the public contribution system for funding new housing,
gradually introduce the leasing of housing, rationalize the ratio
of rent charge to selling price and put more housing on the
market.
</P>
<P>
"We should gradually establish supporting mechanisms for
handling the construction, sales, rental, credit, insurance,
services and property management associated with housing to form a
sound system covering the construction, sales and use of housing,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
China will increase investment in housing for ordinary people
and bring the construction of deluxe commercial housing units and
buildings for high consumption firmly under control.
</P>
<P>
Chen Jinhua also stressed on the importance of developing the
rural market, especially developing and manufacturing agricultural
machinery and improving the quality of such products.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, China will also develop industrial consumer goods
that are suited to the needs of farmers, putting more efforts into
the building of wholesale markets for staple agricultural products
and subsidiary products, Chen said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
