<HEADLINE> Colombian Workers To Protest U.S. Decertification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of workers
will demonstrate next Wednesday in front of the U.S. embassy here
against its disapproval of Colombia's anti-drug policy.
</P>
<P>
Labor sources announced that the demonstration will include a
march through Bogota streets toward the U.S. embassy, in an
eastern section of the Colombian capital.
</P>
<P>
The National Democratic Workers Confederation has invited all
the labor organizations of the country to participate in the
demonstration.
</P>
<P>
The Bill Clinton administration announced Friday its
disapproval of the Colombian anti-drug policies during 1996,
considering that the South American country limited its efforts
against drug trafficking. 
