<HEADLINE> Bruguera, Ivanisevic Vie for Milan Indoor Tennis Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Spain's Sergi Bruguera beat German
Nicolas Kiefer 6-3, 6-4 on Saturday to set up a final clash
against top seed and defending champion Goran Ivanisevic at the
Milan Indoor Tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
Bruguera, ranked 47 in the world, used one hour and five
minutes to roll over Kiefer. Ivanisevic, the Croatian world
number five, beat David Prinosil of Germany 6-0, 7-6 earlier in
the first semi-final match.
</P>
<P>
Kiefer made some unforced errors during the match while the
Spaniard took advantage of that.
</P>
<P>
Kiefer lost his service in the fourth game of the first set
which Bruguera won in just 23 minutes.
</P>
<P>
In the second set, Bruguera never lost his service. The German
had three break points in the fourth game but failed to take the
chances while Bruguera broke Kiefer in the seventh.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's final will be the Spaniard's first since the 1996
Atlanta Olympics when he lost to American Andre Agassi. His last
ATP title was in Prague in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
