<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- All China's major newspapers today
highlighted yesterday's opening ceremony of the fifth session of
the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC) and the government
work report delivered by Premier Li Peng at the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China's leading newspaper, People's Daily, published a
commentary today saying that more proposals put forward by NPC
deputies and members of the CPPCC (Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference) have been adopted.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese president Jiang Zemin said that the western
provinces and autonomous regions should strengthen co-operation
with economically-developed coastal areas so as to narrow the gap
between the economically more developed east and the west.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remark Saturday while joining NPC delegates from
northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region and Gansu Province
to deliberate the government work report.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- Adhering to the basic line of the party is the key point to
promote the construction of socialism with Chinese
Characteristics.
</P>
<P>
