Bureau of CPC (Communist Party of China) Central Committee and
vice-chairman of the Military Commission of the CPC Central
Committee, told PLA (People's Liberation Army) delegates to NPC
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
-- Hu Jintao, member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee and member of the Secretariat of
the Central Committee, asked NPC Tibetan delegates to work for the
economic development and social stability of the country.
</P>
<P>
"Business Weekly"
</P>
<P>
-- Premier Li Peng said in his government work report Saturday
that China plans to maintain good economic growth, improving the
investment structure and deepen reform of state enterprises this
year.
</P>
<P>
He made the speech at the opening ceremony of the fifth session
of the Eighth People's Congress. More than 2,800 delegates are
attending the two-week meeting.
</P>
<P>
-- China's foreign trade is expected to gain more than 10 per
cent this year, and a State Information Center expert predicts
year-round turnover will top 320 billion U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
A customs report on China's trade performance in January said
the country's exports shot up 27.5 per cent last month from a year
ago, indicating the sector had entered a new growth period.
</P>
<P>
-- The Shenzhen Expressway in Guangdong Province will issue 650
million H shares in March to raise 1.2 to 1.4 billion yuan to
build a 44.3 km expressway linking the Shenzhen Airport and He'ao.
</P>
