<HEADLINE> American Retains WBC Lightweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Steve Johnston of the United States
retained his World Boxing Council lightweight title after beating
Jean-BAptiste Mendy of France here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Johnston, 24, took the title with a split decision. Two of the
three judges scored the bout 117-114 and 116-114 in favor of him
while the other judge score the fight 115-114 for Mendy.
</P>
<P>
With the victory, Johnston promoted his unbeaten record to 21
since 1993.
</P>
<P>
Johnston was quicker than Mendy during the first five rounds
though he is 12 centimeters shorter than Mendy.
</P>
<P>
Mendy was penalized a point in the fifth round when he
head-butted Johnston and opened up a cut over the right eyebrow of
Johnston.
</P>
<P>
But Johnston still held on to his advantage in the fight though
he slowed down in the sixth round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
