<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Record Growth of Posts, Telecom in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Telephone lines were extended to
another four counties and 31 townships in southwest China's Tibet
Autonomous Region in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The past year saw the fastest-ever development of the posts and
telecommunications industry in the region, according to Zeng
Zhongyi, director of the regional posts and telecommunications
administration.
</P>
<P>
According to Zeng, the region registered a total business
volume worth 80 million yuan for the sector in 1996, up by 39.3
percent over that of the previous year. The number of local
telephone service users grew by 6,265, pushing the total to
32,794. Meanwhile, the number of mobile phone users grew by 796,
up by 55.98 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The technical level of the facilities has also markedly
improved, Zeng said.
</P>
<P>
Last year two optical cable projects were completed in the
region, extending 512 km. There are nearly 18 telephone users out
of every 100 households in Lhasa city.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
