<HEADLINE> Czech Ice Hockey Head Coach Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Ludek Bukac, head coach of the
Czech national ice hockey team, annouced Friday that he had quit
after series of poor performances of his squad this season.
</P>
<P>
His retirement was just 56 days ahead of the upcoming World
Championships slated for Finland.
</P>
<P>
Bukac, 62, took charge of the former Czech and Slovakia
national team from 1981. The team claimed the world title in two
straight years, in 1985 and 1986, as well as three world
runner-ups and one bronze medal.
</P>
<P>
However, the fortune seemed no longer at their side from this
year. In the total 18 outings, the team only scored three wins
against 13 defeats and two draws. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
