<DOCNO> XIE19970302.0229 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Schwarz Leads in First Day of Safari Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 1 (Xinhua) -- German Armin Schwarz leads on
points having lost time of three hours 17 minutes 40 seconds at
the end of today, an accident-filled first day of the three-day
Safari Rally, round three of the world championship.
</P>
<P>
It's the first time for Schwarz, the 1996 European Rally
Champion, to take part in the African rally regarded widely as the
toughest event on the world championship calendar.
</P>
<P>
Schwarz was followed closely by Britain Richard Burns and Colin
McRae.
</P>
<P>
Finn Tommi Makinen, who won the event last year, was fourth and
Kenyan driver Ian Duncan fifth.
</P>
<P>
World Championship leader Spanish Carlos Sainz and Swedish
Kenneth Eriksson, the winner of the latest round in Sweden, were
forced out of the race due to mechanical problems.
</P>
<P>
Owing to strong winds over the drought-hit plains south of
Nairobi, dust-blindness in overtaking situations has not been a
major factor. Instead, rocks have been the big problem for the
leading cars.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, sand and deep, choking dust have afflicted the
lower-powered 2WD cars and back-markers.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's rally route, the longest leg, covers more than 1,000
kilometers including five competitive sections. It's third
section is smooth, twisty over narrow road and the famous 21
hairpins of the Fluospar climb. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970302.0230 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Man Removed of Huge Facial Angioma </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Yang Yunguang, a man of the Hani
ethnic group in Hani-Yi Autonomous Prefecture of Honghe in Yunnan
Province, has become an ordinary-looking man again after removing
a huge tumor (angioma) from his face in the prefectural hospital.
</P>
<P>
Yang, a farmer, also suffered from epilepsy. The tumor covered
two thirds of his face. Shunned by others, he stayed at home as
much as possible.
</P>
<P>
Yang was spotted in late 1996 by Zhu Peisuo, deputy head of the
prefectural hospital, who had gone to Honghe to spread knowledge
of health care.
</P>
<P>
Supported by the prefecture's science and technology
commission, nationalities affairs commission and public health
bureau, the Honghe Prefectural Hospital decided to perform surgery
on Yang, with the Honghe County government and the hospital
sharing the charges.
</P>
<P>
The operation lasted nearly 20 hours, and Yang's face was
restored to normal by plastic surgery in January this year.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
