<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hainan Becoming Chin's Winter Tourist Resort </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The unique tropical island scenery
of south China's Hainan Province has helped make it China's
tourist resort in winter when northern parts of the country are
battered by icy winds and blizzards.
</P>
<P>
The island province has summer year-round. After several years
of construction work, Hainan now has better quality tourism
facilities with tropical characteristics in the cities of Haikou
and Sanya, attracting many tourists from different parts of China.
</P>
<P>
From February 1 to 15, the traditional Spring Festival holiday
period, the airport at Haikou, the provincial capital, handled
180,000 passengers, a rise of 65,000 people or 23 percent over the
same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The province had 4.86 million tourists in 1996, an increase of
34.6 percent over the previous year, according to local officials,
who say that the province will increase efforts to create new
tourist programs and improve tourist facilities, and will try to
have five million tourists this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
