<HEADLINE> Renaud Breaks Short-course Swimming World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Chris Renaud of Canada broke the
men's 50-meter backstroke short-course swimming world record at
St. Catharines, Canada, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Renaud clocked 24.25 seconds to beat the previous record of
24.37 held by American Jeff Rouse at the Canadian Interuniversity
Athletic Union swimming championships.
</P>
<P>
The previous world record was set by Jeff Rouse at a World Cup
meet in February 1995. 
</P>
