<HEADLINE> Documentary in Yi Language Celebrates Deng Xiaoping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, March 2 (Xinhua) -- "We miss Deng Xiaoping and will
remember his words and smiles forever," said a farmer of the Yi
nationality with tears in his eyes in Sichuan province. This was
the first time for him to understand what Deng said totally by
watching the TV documentary "Deng Xiaoping" dubbed in his own
language.
</P>
<P>
The province recently translated the TV series "Deng Xiaoping"
into the Yi language to mark the death of the senior Chinese
leader.
</P>
<P>
Local culture departments overcame the difficulty of having no
script, and only spent a few days completing the language
translation work for the first part of the documentary.
</P>
<P>
There are more than one million Yi people in the
province. Local farmers, who are leading better lives today,
expressed their heartfelt thanks for the reform and opening-up
policies initiated by Deng. 
</P>
</TEXT>
