<DOCNO> XIE19970302.0245 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 21:59 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey Tries to Enter EU in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Foreign Minister Tansu
Ciller said today that Turkey is trying to enter the European
Union in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Ciller, also deputy prime minister, told the Turkish
determination to the U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright
and Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi today whey she had
telephone talks with them.
</P>
<P>
She told the U.S. and Italian officials that one of Turkey's main
objectives for 1997 would be put on the list of nations vying for
early full membership into the EU.
</P>
<P>
She later told reporters that "Turkey will take its place among
the big nations".
</P>
<P>
A statement issued early this morning by the Turkish Foreign
Ministry said that the National Security Council, which held a
nine-hour meeting Friday, had recommended that Turkey's early
accession onto the EU's membership list should be made a priority
for the present government.
</P>
<P>
"This means that Turkey's drive for full membership has been
underscored at the highest organ of the country as a state
policy," said the statement.
</P>
<P>
It added, "Turkey will maintain its determined efforts aimed
at integration with the EU in line with this policy."
</P>
<P>
The statement pointed out that Ciller will continue to hold a
series of such talks with other western colleagues in the coming
days in a bid to gain support for Turkey's entry into the EU.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
