<HEADLINE> Sudanese President Calls for More Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Sudanese President Omer Hassan
Ahmed al-Bashir called for expanding cooperation between China
and Sudan in all fields, stressing that the ties of friendship
between the two countries are deep-rooted and excellent.
</P>
<P>
The president made the remarks he met here today with Wu Yaowen,
President of China National Petroleum Corporation.
</P>
<P>
Wu is currently visiting Sudan at the head of an economic
delegation to examine with Sudanese officials details of a
Sudanese oil project with a cost of 1 billion U.S. dollars to
be financed by companies from China, Malaysia and Canada.
</P>
<P>
The execution of the project is expected to begin later this
year.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this week, the Sudanese president expressed optimism
over the possibility of developing the oil industry in his
country, announcing that Sudan would start exporting oil in
1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
