<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yemen Holds First National Conference on Women </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Yemen's First National Conference on
Women opened here today to discuss how to involve women in decision
making.
</P>
<P>
In a speech making at the opening session of the conference,
Yemeni President Ali Abdullah Saleh said that the Yemeni
government would give all attention to the equality between men
and women, calling on women to contribute actively to the process
of development.
</P>
<P>
Saleh also called on Prime Minister Abdul Aziz Abdul Ghani to
enable women to hold posts of all levels according to their
efficiency and ability.
</P>
<P>
The idea of holding this conference dates back to 1995 when
Yemen participated in the international day on women held then in
the Chinese capital Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
